    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-24T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="689"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/7–2446: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="80" xml:id="d689fn80">Cabled to the other governments named in the
                        February <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> resolution as members of
                        the Preparatory Committee for the trade and employment conference.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-24T08:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1946—8 a. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You wall shortly receive third person air mail instruction<note n="81"
                        xml:id="d689fn81">Fourteen of the instructions were sent out under date of
                        July 25 (560.AL/7–2546). Four of the instructions, despatched to United
                        States missions in the Western Pacific and South African areas, were sent
                        out under date of July 26 (560.AL/7–2646). These documents necessarily were
                        received by the different missions and so transmitted to the different
                        governments at varying times. See footnote 85, <ref target="#pg_1342">p.
                            1342</ref>.</note> enclosing copies Draft Charter of International Trade
                    Organization and explanatory covering memo. After clearance from Dept, which you
                    will receive by telegraph, please hand copies Draft Charter to <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">Fonoff</gloss> together with statement along lines of
                    covering memo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
